<span id="freeTextContainer10546669049669907221">I couldn&apos;t even get through this book. The information was poorly organized and it just wasn&apos;t very good reading. It was recommended on Michael Moore&apos;s website a while back.<br/><br/>The premise of the book sounded interesting to me and Michael Moore&apos;s heart is in the right place, but the book is just utter rubbish. It&apos;s not for serious thinkers who are looking for something insightful and revealing about US culture. <br/></span>
  <span id="freeText10546669049669907221" style="display:none">I couldn't even get through this book. The information was poorly organized and it just wasn't very good reading. It was recommended on Michael Moore's website a while back.<br /><br />The premise of the book sounded interesting to me and Michael Moore's heart is in the right place, but the book is just utter rubbish. It's not for serious thinkers who are looking for something insightful and revealing about US culture. <br /></span>
