<span id="freeTextContainer2976405683795041564">This book is all about how modern day fears are stoked by the media. Although I knew much of the big ideas being brought forward in this book, I appreciated the concrete facts which backed up the propositions. Unfortunately I was reading a copy published in 1999, and there is a newer version that came out around 2010. My guess is that much of the text is the same, but that many of the examples come from more current times. I would also imagine that the post-9/11 world has made a big impact on ou</span>
  <span id="freeText2976405683795041564" style="display:none">This book is all about how modern day fears are stoked by the media. Although I knew much of the big ideas being brought forward in this book, I appreciated the concrete facts which backed up the propositions. Unfortunately I was reading a copy published in 1999, and there is a newer version that came out around 2010. My guess is that much of the text is the same, but that many of the examples come from more current times. I would also imagine that the post-9/11 world has made a big impact on our fears. What was interesting was just how relevant all these insights are today, in spite being researched and written 20 years ago. If you are like me and have family members who seem to be fearful of everything in the world these days, this book will provide you with lots of good information with which to counter those fears.</span>
