        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer943078777" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16731173395729045880">This message was important when the book was published. It is just historical non-fiction now. You could argue that it&apos;s gone beyond and, uh, off the cliff.<br/><br/>The people giving it one star don&apos;t get or don&apos;t want to get it. And those criticizing it for being slanted--I don&apos;t remember being so polarized back then either. <br/><br/>The premise of the book is a general truth through time--advertising has used fear as a tactic to sell always. And on and on...what is negative political advertising during campaign</span>
  <span id="freeText16731173395729045880" style="display:none">This message was important when the book was published. It is just historical non-fiction now. You could argue that it's gone beyond and, uh, off the cliff.<br /><br />The people giving it one star don't get or don't want to get it. And those criticizing it for being slanted--I don't remember being so polarized back then either. <br /><br />The premise of the book is a general truth through time--advertising has used fear as a tactic to sell always. And on and on...what is negative political advertising during campaign season? Some people just don't want to open their eyes.</span>
